  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A debit is an entry on the left side of an [account](./account.md); a credit is an entry on the right side. In [double-entry bookkeeping](./double-entry-bookkeeping.md), every transaction consists of equal debits and credits — if $500 is debited somewhere, $500 must be credited elsewhere.",
